OL,3,GGrampian
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mainly dry, bright morning.
OL,6,FCloud will bubble up through the day
OL,7,Fto give a few afternoon showers
OL,8,Finland, while the east coast will be
OL,9,Flargely sunny.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FMainly dry with late sunny
OL,12,Fspells this evening, any showers in
OL,13,Fthe west dying out. Turning rather
OL,14,Fcloudy through the night with patchy
OL,15,Frain arriving in the west towards dawn.
OL,16,
OL,17,CTuesday:FOvercast with patchy rain
OL,18,Fwhich may turn occasionally heavy for
OL,19,Fa time. Moray will see the best of the
OL,20,Fdrier and brighter conditions. Fresh
OL,21,Fwinds, strong on the east coast.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
